  • Classes in com.tymeac.base used by com.tymeac.base 
    Class and Description
    AreaBase
    The Queue Area contains Queue-wide variables the reflect.method pointer to the Processing Application Class the pointer to the waitlist anchor the pointer to the queue threads anchor The Queue structure: level 1 -- AreaBase (this) level 2a -- AreaThreadsAnchor level 3a -- AreaThreadMgmt level 2b -- AreaWaitListsAnchor level 3b -- AreaWaitList
    AreaBasicThread
    Queue Thread base logic
    AreaList
    This is just the list of all Tymeac Queues.
    AreaThreadMgmt
    This is the management storage for a Queue's thread.
    AreaThreadsAnchor
    This is the anchor point for the Queue's thread Classes.
    AreaWaitList
    A single Queue Wait List.
    AreaWaitListsAnchor
    This is the anchor point for the Queue's Wait Lists The pool is simply an ArrayList.
    BaseServer
    Tymeac Server base class
    CancelParm
    Class for encapsulating the fields necessary to to cancel a syncReq().
    ClsUrl
    Hold a complex name as its component URL and Class
    CSFServer
    This is the non-activatable rmi server using custom socket factories
    FuncDetail
    A Tymeac Function detail object
    FuncHeader
    Tymeac Function header contains the Function array setup, the search methods for finding an entry and the methods for accessing the detail array.
    GenTable
    Generated numbers for both a sync and async request
    InterruptionReady
    Interface for notifying a callback client that the syncRequest() interruption is available.
    Monitor
    The Tymeac Monitor
    RequestDetail
    A request detail object.
    RequestHeader
    The object that holds the request details array
    RMIServer
    This is the non-activatable rmi server
    StallDetail
    The stall array detail class.
    StallHeader
    The stall array header.
    Startup
    Tymeac Server Start up base module.
    StartupFields
    These are the fields used by the start up classes.
    TyAltSvrElements
    This class contains the objects for the Alter Server Options client.
    TyBase
    The base storage for all Tymeac processing.
    TyCfgFields
    For passing string from the config file fetch method to the start up main method
    TyClassLoader
    Class loader for Strings
    TyLogTable
    Tymeac logging may be thru a DBMS, a local file, or a user method
    TyLogThread
    Tymeac logging thread
    TymeacAlternativesInterface
    This is the Interface for the Statistics and Log methods
    TymeacCancelParm
    This structure holds the Server sync request info so that the Server Internal Processing Application Class may pass a CancelParm Object back to the Client.
    TymeacIIOPImpl
    This class is identical to com.tymeac.base.TymeacStandardImpl except that this class extends PortableRemoteObject.
    TymeacImpl
    This is the main implementation logic for the Tymeac Server.
    TymeacIndividualFunction
    This is the Class for Individual User Function See also TyIndividualQueue
    TymeacIndividualQueue
    This is the Class for an Individual User Queue See also TymeacIndividualQueue
    TymeacInfo
    This Singleton class contains information about the currently executing Tymeac Server.
    TymeacInterface
    The interface for the Tymeac Server
    TymeacLogin
    The login interface for the Tymeac Server.
    TymeacLoginImpl
    RMI implementation of Tymeac Login interface
    TymeacParm
    This is the parameter passed to the Tymeac Server from Clients.
    TymeacPOAImpl
    This class is identical to com.tymeac.base.TymeacIIOPImpl except that this class is for the Portable Object Adapter and requires rmic with the -poa option.
    TymeacReturn
    This class reformates the return objects from both a syncRequest() and asyncRequest() into the components internal to the return Object[].
    TyNotifyTable
    Notification logic
    TyOverallObj
    This class is the return object for an overall status request.
    TyParm
    Class used by diagnose method in the IMPL class
    TyQueElements
    Used for the Que Data GUI
    TyRunTimeElements
    Used for the Run Time Functions GUI
    TyStatsTable
    Tymeac statistics writing may be thru a DBMS, a local file, or a user method
    TyStatsThread
    Tymeac stats writter thread.
    TyWLElements
    The Queue Wait Lists passed information
